# This is a marker file for zsh-python-module-completion plugin
#
# When this file (named .local_module_completion) exists in your Python project root,
# the plugin will scan local modules in your project for completion.
#
# Without this file, zsh's default Python module completion will be used instead,
# which shows installed packages from your Python environment.
#
# To enable local module completion in your project:
#   cp .local_module_completion.example .local_module_completion
# Or simply:
#   touch .local_module_completion
#
# You can add this file to your .gitignore if you don't want to commit it,
# or commit it to enable local completion for all project contributors.
